<hr>
<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
The Chicago style does not include newspaper articles in the bibliography. All details are included in the footnote. However, some tutor or lecturers may require you to add an entry in the bibliography. When there is no author the title of the newspaper stands in place of the author. An example is provided below. Chicago does not recommend using page numbers for newspaper articles but a section number or edition could be included. For an article publicly accessible on the internet, include the URL at the end of the citation after the year.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em>Newspaper Title</em>, &#34;Title of Article.&#34; Month day, year of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Newspaper Title">Herald Tribune</span></em>, 
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Article">Professor to Talk Rubbish at Next Senate Meeting</span>.&#34; 
	<span class="hover" title="Month day, year of publication">December 15, 2056</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
